cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cellular network optimization and user association policies. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves maximizing network utility and downlink rates. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses proportional fairness utility and optimization problems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper involves resource allocation and optimization in a system of base stations and mobile users. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses both centralized and distributed algorithms for user association.
